 energy will\ndivide that energy between spatial scales such that low-wavenumber power is\noverestimated, and high-wavenumber power is underestimated relative to a\ncomparable system possessing higher Rayleigh number. We discuss the\nimplications of these results in light of the current inconsistencies between\nmodels and observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 7 Nov 2015 20:24:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-02-17"}
